article.headline: Army 66, Texas-Pan American 58
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Julian Simmons scored 18 points Wednesday night to lead Army to a 66-58 victory over Texas-Pan American. Jeremy Hence scored 12 points for the Black Knights (7-6). Army was 11 for 27 from 3-point range, with Simmons going 5 for 9 and Hence 4 for 7. Perry Petty led the Broncs (3-12) with 21 points. Brandon Provost added 15. It was the first meeting between the schools. Texas-Pan American hits the road for its next seven games before playing at home again Feb. 3 against Utah Valley.
